data.meta_description: Jul 25, 2024 - Inge Morath, born in Graz, Austria, initially studied languages in Berlin before becoming a journalist and editor for Heute in Munich. Collaborating with Ernst Haas, she transitioned to photography, joining Magnum Photos in 1953. Morath's career began in London in 1951, marking the start of her influential work capturing diverse subjects with her distinctive style. See more ideas about inge morath, magnum photos, photography.
